### TerraFab™ Node Specification – One Complete 3 nm → 1.4 nm Fab (30 000 wspm)

| Category                     | 2034 Specification                                           | % Mass Waste-Derived Ceramic | 2025 Precedent                                 |
|------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| Cleanroom Envelope           | 4 800 m² ISO-2 ballroom, ceramic walls/floor/ceiling         | 96 %                       | Large porcelain panel plants (Florim, Laminam) |
| Lithography                  | 4 × ASML NXE:3600D + 2 × High-NA EXE:5000 in ceramic pods    | 38–44 %                    | Standard ASML tools + ceramic shielding        |
| Dry Etch                     | 18 × full-ceramic SiC/Y₂O₃ chambers                          | 89 %                       | Lam CeramiX + CoorsTek full-chamber pilots     |
| CVD / ALD                    | 14 × TerraCVD™/TerraALD™ hot-wall ceramic reactors           | 92 %                       | Applied Materials Olympia ALD with ceramic kit |
| Ion Implant                 | 5 × standard tools with full ceramic beamline & shielding    | 72 %                       | Sumitomo ceramic beamline prototypes           |
| Wet Processing               | 16 × ZrO₂ single-wafer + batch wet benches                   | 94 %                       | 2025 ceramic-coated wet benches → full ceramic    |
| Metrology & Inspection       | CD-SEM, overlay, review tools on ceramic stages              | 85 %                       | KLA/Zeiss with ceramic air-bearing stages      |
| Utilities & Support          | 800 V DC microgrid + Genesis-Nano™ on-fab gas/water loop      | 97 %                       | Ceramic heat exchangers + AWG proven           |
| Assembly & Maintenance Swarm | 182 × TerraBot™ Mk3 (45 kg payload, ISO-14644-1 clean)        | 100 % waste-derived frame  | UR20 + ABB GoFa with ceramic arms              |

### Ceramic Purity Tiers (2034 Realistic)

| Tier | Purity           | Source                                      | Application                              | % of Total Fab Mass |
|------|------------------|---------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------|---------------------|
| A    | 96–99.5 %        | 100 % vitrified waste + fly ash             | Walls, floors, structural liners         | 76 %                |
| B    | 99.97–99.99 %    | Waste + electrolytic refining               | Chucks, showerheads, non-optical parts   | 19 %                |
| C    | 99.999–99.9999 % | 50–70 % waste + 30–50 % virgin precursors   | EUV mirror blanks, gate tools            | 4.8 %               |
| D    | 99.99999 %       | Closed-loop recycled mirrors (post-2042)    | Future nodes                             | <0.2 %              |

