### Revenue Model (One Node – 20 Years)

| Stream                          | Amount (2034 USD)      | Gross Margin |
|---------------------------------|--------------------------|--------------|
| Upfront kit hardware            | $2.822 B                 | 69 %         |
| 20-year lease & support         | $2.46 B ($123 M/yr)      | 89 %         |
| **Total revenue per node**           | **$5.282 B**             | **78 % avg** |

One Genesis factory at full capacity (2031) supplies ceramic content for ~9–11 TerraFab™ nodes per year → $45–55 B annual recurring profit from 2038 onward.

### Mandatory Realism & Compliance Constraints
- No thick batteries or supercapacitors on panels  
- No quantum-encrypted lock-in or anti-right-to-repair features  
- Full compliance with SEMI S2/S8/F47, U.S. ECCN, and ITAR/EAR  
- All tools must pass qualification at TSMC/GlobalFoundries/Intel/Samsung by 2033  
- Yield target: 93–96 % at 3 nm (ceramic reduces metallic & organic contamination only)

